events.name: Northwestern State Demons at LSU Tigers

headlines.description: Spencer Ware and Michael Ford ran for two scores apiece and second-ranked LSU overwhelmed Northwestern State 49-3 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 2 LSU wins in romp

events.name: Alabama Crimson Tide at Penn State Nittany Lions

headlines.description: AJ McCarron was poised and efficient in a rare trip into Big Ten country for No. 3 Alabama, throwing for 163 yards and a touchdown against No. 23 Penn State in a 27-11 victory on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Alabama rolls Penn St.

events.name: Charleston Southern Buccaneers at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: EJ Manuel threw for a career-best 329 yards and four touchdowns Saturday as No. 5 Florida State defeated Charleston Southern 62-10 in a tune-up for next week's showdown against top-ranked Oklahoma.
headlines.shortLinkText: Manuel has career day to help Florida St. roll

events.name: Stanford Cardinal at Duke Blue Devils

headlines.description: Andrew Luck matched a career high by throwing four touchdown passes in No. 6 Stanford's 44-14 rout of Duke on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luck throws 4 TDs as Stanford romps past Duke

events.name: Oregon State Beavers at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: Russell Wilson threw three touchdowns and No. 8 Wisconsin overcame a slow start from its running game to beat Oregon State 35-0 at Camp Randall Stadium on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wisconsin cruises in shutout of Oregon State

events.name: Fresno State Bulldogs at Nebraska Cornhuskers

headlines.description: Ameer Abdullah returned a kickoff 100 yards after Fresno State made it a two-point game in the fourth quarter, and Taylor Martinez's 46-yard touchdown run secured the 10th-ranked Cornhuskers' 42-29 victory on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nebraska pulls away from Fresno State in fourth

events.name: Virginia Tech Hokies at East Carolina Pirates

headlines.description: Josh Oglesby ran for the go-ahead 10-yard score with 7:30 left, helping No. 11 Virginia Tech beat East Carolina 17-10 on Saturday to give coach Frank Beamer his 200th win at the school.
headlines.shortLinkText: Va. Tech gives Beamer milestone

events.name: South Carolina Gamecocks at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description: South Carolina scored twice off turnovers, including defensive end Melvin Ingram's second touchdown with 3:12 remaining, and the No. 12 Gamecocks beat mistake-prone Georgia 45-42 Saturday for the early lead in the Southeastern Conference East.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia turnovers help S. Carolina win  on road

events.name: Nevada Wolf Pack at Oregon Ducks

headlines.description: Darron Thomas matched a school record with six touchdown passes and No. 13 Oregon bounced back from its season-opening loss to beat Nevada 69-20 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ducks' Thomas throws 6 TDs

events.name: New Mexico Lobos at Arkansas Razorbacks

headlines.description: Tyler Wilson threw for 259 yards and accounted for a pair of touchdowns as No. 14 Arkansas defeated New Mexico 52-3 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kickoff return helps Arkansas whip New Mexico

events.name: Toledo Rockets at Ohio State Buckeyes

headlines.description: Chris Fields returned a punt 69 yards and Carlos Hyde ran for two more scores to lead No. 15 Ohio State past Toledo 27-22 Saturday, a win that was secure only after the Buckeyes held the Rockets' on their last drive.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ohio St. staves off Toledo

events.name: Mississippi State Bulldogs at Auburn Tigers

headlines.description: Ryan Smith stopped Chris Relf at the goal line on the final play to preserve Auburn's 41-34 win over No. 16 Mississippi State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Auburn stuffs Mississippi State

events.name: Florida Atlantic Owls at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: Kirk Cousins threw for 183 yards and two touchdowns, and No. 17 Michigan State held Florida Atlantic to one first down in a 44-0 victory over the Owls on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Michigan St. shuts out FAU

events.name: UAB Blazers at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Chris Rainey ran for 119 yards and a touchdown, Caleb Sturgis kicked three field goals after the offense bogged down and No. 18 Florida beat UAB 39-0 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rainey leads Florida in tuneup victory over UAB

events.name: Norfolk State Spartans at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.description: Geno Smith threw for 371 yards and four scores and West Virginia overcame a rough start to beat Norfolk State 55-12 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: W. Virginia wakes up in 2nd half

events.name: Ball State Cardinals at South Florida Bulls

headlines.description: B.J. Daniels threw for a career-best 359 yards and one touchdown Saturday night, leading No. 22 South Florida to a 37-7 rout of Ball State.
headlines.shortLinkText: Daniels' big day leads South Florida in laugher

events.name: BYU Cougars at Texas Longhorns

headlines.description: Backup quarterbacks Case McCoy and David Ash pumped new life into a struggling Texas offense and Cody Johnson scored a fourth-quarter touchdown as the No. 24 Longhorns rallied to beat BYU 17-16 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Backup QBs power Texas

events.name: TCU Horned Frogs at Air Force Falcons

headlines.description: The 25th-ranked TCU Horned Frogs brushed off their Baylor blues and routed Air Force 35-19 Saturday for their 18th straight win in the Mountain West Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: TCU bounces back from loss to wallop Air Force

events.name: Iowa Hawkeyes at Iowa State Cyclones

headlines.description: James White's 4-yard TD run in triple overtime pushed Iowa State past rival Iowa 44-41 on Saturday, snapping a three-game losing streak to the rival Hawkeyes in thrilling fashion.
headlines.shortLinkText: Iowa State floors rival Iowa in triple OT stunner

events.name: Central Michigan Chippewas at Kentucky Wildcats

headlines.description: Josh Clemons scored on an 87-yard run, and Morgan Newton ran in a fourth-quarter touchdown to seal Kentucky's 27-13 comeback win over Central Michigan on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clemens, Newton fuel Kentucky's comeback win

events.name: San Diego State Aztecs at Army Black Knights

headlines.shortLinkText: Hillman's 2 TDs lead San Diego State past Army

events.name: South Dakota State Jackrabbits at Illinois Fighting Illini

headlines.description: Freshman running back Donovonn Young introduced himself to Illinois fans with a pair of touchdowns and Nathan Scheelhaase ran for two more on Saturday in a 56-3 blowout over South Dakota State.
headlines.shortLinkText: Freshman RB Young scores twice as Illini roll

events.name: Old Dominion Monarchs at Georgia State Panthers
Rutgers Scarlet Knights at North Carolina Tar Heels

headlines.description: Giovani Bernard rushed for 81 yards and two touchdowns to help North Carolina beat Rutgers 24-22 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bernard helps sloppy UNC overtake Rutgers

events.name: Maine Black Bears at Pittsburgh Panthers

headlines.description: Ray Graham ran for 121 yards and three touchdowns to lead Pittsburgh past Maine 35-29 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Graham (3 TDs), Pittsburgh hold off Maine rally

California Golden Bears at Colorado Buffaloes

headlines.description: Keenan Allen hauled in a 5-yard TD pass from Zach Maynard in overtime, lifting California to a thrilling 36-33 win over Colorado on Saturday despite a record-setting offensive day by the Buffaloes.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cal emerges in OT despite Colorado's huge day

events.name: Eastern Illinois Panthers at Northwestern Wildcats

headlines.shortLinkText: Clter leads Northwestern's rout of E. Illinois

events.name: New Mexico State Aggies at Minnesota Golden Gophers

headlines.description: New Mexico State's 28-21 victory at Minnesota on Saturday afternoon was overshadowed by a health scare for Gophers head coach Jerry Kill, who had an apparent seizure on the sideline..
headlines.shortLinkText: NM State's win clouded by Minn. coach's scare

events.name: NC State Wolfpack at Wake Forest Demon Deacons

headlines.description: Danny Dembry had two TDs and Tanner Price threw for 297 yards and a touchdown as Wake Forest held off North Carolina State 34-27 on Saturday in the Atlantic Coast Conference opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dembry, Price lead Wake Forest past NC State

events.name: Wofford Terriers at Clemson Tigers

headlines.description: Tajh Boyd threw three touchdowns and Andre Ellington ran for 165 yards as Clemson held on for a 35-27 victory over Wofford on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clemson needs Boyd's 3 TDs to get by Wofford

Cincinnati Bearcats at Tennessee Volunteers

headlines.description: Tyler Bray threw for a career-high 405 yards, passed for four touchdowns and ran for a fifth score as Tennessee cruised to a 45-23 win over Cincinnati on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bray throws 4 TDs, runs for another as Vols roll

events.name: Rhode Island Rams at Syracuse Orange

headlines.description: Ryan Nassib threw for a career-high 318 yards and three touchdowns, including the decisive one to walk-on Michael Acchione midway through the fourth quarter, and Syracuse held off game Rhode Island 21-14 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Syracuse holds off upset-minded Rhode Island

events.name: San Jose State Spartans at UCLA Bruins

headlines.description: Derrick Coleman rushed for 135 yards -- all in the second half -- and UCLA survived a lackluster performance to beat San Jose State 27-17 Saturday night, handing the Spartans their 24th loss in 27 games dating back to the beginning of the 2009 season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coleman helps UCLA overcome San Jose St.
